- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper describes the control and evaluation of a biped robot, which falls under the robotics field. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the design and control of a complex system, which involves various control algorithms and stability analysis. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper describes the design of a new system for actuation, which involves mechanical engineering principles. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper mentions the use of algorithms for position and force control, which falls under the AI field. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although not a major focus of the paper, computer vision may be used in the future for the biped robot to perceive its environment and improve its walking performance.
